  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess the feasibility, safety and short term effects on
      health related quality of life, of maintaining hemoglobin from 120 to 130 g/L versus from 100
      to 110 g/L, with red cell concentrate (RCC) transfusion, in women having chemo-radiation for
      cancer of the cervix.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
